{"key":"post-13523300","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13523300</id>\n<content>The made in china crap for hygrometers they pass off on us now are worthless.&amp;nbsp; None are accurate over more than a very small scale.&amp;nbsp; If it reads 100% when wrapped in a damp towel, and 80% when in a dry room doesn't surprise me at all.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Mist your substrates, and if the water evaporates completely in 20 to 30 minutes, your humidity is OK.&amp;nbsp; If it evaporates after only ten minutes, your area is too dry.&amp;nbsp; If they're still wet after more than 30 minutes, increase fresh air supply.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;I grow commercially and don't even use hygrometers in my farm, because they're crap these days and I won't waste any more money on them.&amp;nbsp; I judge humidity by the above.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13523317</next>\n<prev>13523259</prev>\n<first>13523259</first>\n<last>13523339</last>\n<when>1290442989</when>\n<utime>11/22/10 06:23 PM</utime>\n</post>"}